{"sequence":21,"timestamp":"2026-04-13T08:58:15.212857707Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-73a64a77","body":"finding_summary: Planning and `plan_and_implement` stage overrides can still silently drop the new scope guidance. `build_stage_prompt()` only computes the guidance block for those stages (`src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:166-174`), but stage templates still treat `classification_guidance` as optional (`src/contexts/workspace_governance/template_catalog.rs:406-413,766-774`). The new regression test explicitly accepts a `plan_and_implement.md` override that omits the placeholder (`tests/unit/prompt_builder_test.rs:655-704`), so any existing workspace/project override will continue generating scope-unaware prompts even when the bead task prompt contract is present. That misses the acceptance criterion that these stages receive scope-aware guidance whenever bead scope sections exist. severity: medium. affected_files: src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs, src/contexts/workspace_governance/template_catalog.rs, tests/unit/prompt_builder_test.rs. remediation_hint: require `{{classification_guidance}}` for planning-oriented overrides when the bead contract is active, or inject the scope guidance outside template-controlled content so overrides cannot suppress it.","dedup_key":"bf890d58c3ebb8cea179e1c228f12cef330f44048dd97cb2903b031d6a0da0e8","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260413084713","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
