{"sequence":49,"timestamp":"2026-04-13T15:30:13.985184887Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-01747c85","body":"fix-now: `render_scope_guidance()` is reusing the reviewer-facing `extract_pe_bead_ids()` helper, so the planning prompt enumerates short aliases like `alpha` in addition to canonical bead IDs (`src/contexts/workflow_composition/review_classification.rs:483-510`, `src/contexts/project_run_record/task_prompt_contract.rs:271-305`). That helper is explicitly designed for review-time `mapped_to_bead_id` matching, not for planner-facing guidance, and it deduplicates aliases in a set. In scope guidance this creates two correctness problems: planners can defer work to an ID that does not actually exist in the bead graph, and two different planned-elsewhere beads with the same short suffix collapse into one ambiguous alias. The new test also bakes this behavior in by asserting alias output (`src/contexts/workflow_composition/review_classification.rs:1578-1603`). Severity: medium. Affected files: `src/contexts/workflow_composition/review_classification.rs`, `src/contexts/project_run_record/task_prompt_contract.rs`. Remediation hint: render only the canonical bead IDs that actually appear in the `Already Planned Elsewhere` section for planning/scope guidance, or explicitly label any alias list as reviewer-only and keep it out of planner prompts.","dedup_key":"e6c30ec7226c048651a226dab5b59096cad453cf88b8882ce0075db99d57e3dd","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260413084713","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
