{"sequence":79,"timestamp":"2026-04-13T15:52:42.316197065Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-bfd4b428","body":"finding_summary: `render_scope_guidance()` emits `## Scope Guidance` for any prompt that merely has the contract marker, even if the bead scope sections are absent. The new gate at [src/contexts/workflow_composition/review_classification.rs:478-483] only checks `prompt_uses_contract()`, and `prompt_uses_contract()` is intentionally true for marker-only/drifted prompts [src/contexts/project_run_record/task_prompt_contract.rs:123-124], as the existing test at [src/contexts/project_run_record/task_prompt_contract.rs:419-428] shows. That means Planning/PlanAndImplement can now tell the model to obey `Must-Do Scope`, `Explicit Non-Goals`, and `Acceptance Criteria` sections that are not actually present, which violates the backward-compat requirement for prompts with no bead-scope sections.\nseverity: low\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/workflow_composition/review_classification.rs\n- tests/unit/prompt_builder_test.rs\nremediation_hint: Only emit scope guidance when the prompt actually contains the canonical scope section headings (or passes canonical prompt-shape validation), and add a regression test for a contract-marker prompt missing those sections.","dedup_key":"e04c5a7c89311b7754de6035e69d7f98576fa07f2ef8e9853bca7f372dbb95fd","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260413084713","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
