{"sequence":100,"timestamp":"2026-04-13T16:04:22.020697163Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-9bf4eb27","body":"finding_summary: The legacy fallback for planning/plan-and-implement scope guidance can splice `## Scope Guidance` into the middle of `{{project_prompt}}` instead of before the stage schema. `inject_scope_guidance()` searches the fully rendered prompt for the first `\\n## Authoritative JSON Schema` and inserts there (src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:209-224). A bead prompt can legitimately contain that same heading inside `AGENTS / Repo Guidance`, because `render_bead_task_prompt()` only escapes canonical contract headings and leaves other `## ...` headings untouched (src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs:769-798). On a supported legacy override that omits `{{classification_guidance}}`, this corrupts the prompt structure and weakens the new scope-boundary instructions.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs\n- src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs\nremediation_hint: Inject relative to template structure instead of searching the rendered prompt text, or at minimum make the fallback target the final schema section unambiguously and add a regression test with `## Authoritative JSON Schema` inside repo guidance.","dedup_key":"87065ed8e292cf16529e997f83af17e7c0aeceee82d714fbd113a19973e43316","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260413084713","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
